<p>Updating a work package</p><p>Move a work package into the next state of the work flow, adjust
	 hours assigned, add approvals, or edit other information. 
  </p> 
	  
		<ul> 
		   
			 Know and understand the work
				flow for the product. 
			  
		   
		   
			 If the work package uses CMS
				content, ensure the impacted topics are checked back into the CMS, so that the
				most recent version of the content is available for the next state in the work
				flow. 
			  
		   
		 
	 </ul> 
	  
		<p>Update work packages to transition
		  to the next state in the work flow, adjust the hours, or edit other work
		  package details. 
		</p> 
	  
	  
		 
		  Find the desired work package in 
			 My Work or on the 
			 Work Packages tab. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Update. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Make the desired changes to the work package. 
		   
		   
			 <p>Changes might include: 
			 <ul> 
				 
				  Moving the work package to
					 the next state of the work flow. 
				   
				 
				 
				  Declaring your approval of
					 the content associated with the work package. 
				   
				 
				 
				  Adjusting the hours spent
					 on the current stage of the work flow. 
				   
				 
				 
				  Adding a note to the work
					 package information. 
				   
				 
			  
			 </ul> 
		  </p> 
		  If you are approving the content, you must select the next 
			 State in the work flow, and then select an 
			 Approval option. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Save. 
		   
		 
	  
		<p> The work package is updated. 
		</p> 
	  
  